# Cabin Scheduling App — Project Context

## What This App Does

Scheduling and booking tool for 5–15 cabin co-owners:
- View shared calendar showing who has the cabin and when
- Book, swap, and assign time slots
- Add notes to bookings
- Works on desktop and mobile browser
- Runs in Docker; PostgreSQL database via Prisma

## Repository Layout

```
apps/api/     Fastify + Prisma (PostgreSQL)
apps/web/     React + Vite
docker/       Entrypoint: migrate, seed, start
```

Do not add new top-level directories without a clear reason. New features go inside the existing apps.

## Quality Checks

Run these before asking for a new feature. Fix errors before adding more code.

| Check | Command |
|---|---|
| Lint | `pnpm lint` |
| Type errors | `pnpm tsc --noEmit` |
| Format | `pnpm format` |
| Tests | `pnpm test` |

## Feature Checklist — Before Calling Something Done

- [ ] Happy path works in the browser
- [ ] Bad input is handled (empty fields, invalid dates, past dates)
- [ ] Works on a phone-sized screen
- [ ] User has an obvious way to undo a mistake
- [ ] `pnpm lint` and `pnpm tsc` pass

## If a Suggestion Feels Too Complex

Say: *"This seems more complex than needed for a 10-person cabin app. What's the simplest version that would still work? What are we giving up by going simpler?"*

The AI defaults to patterns from large production systems. This project does not need them.
